-- 
CER Board Recommends That Securityholders Vote for Resolutions

-- B y   C o l i n   K e a t i n g e
-- 
2011-10-05T08:32:50Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-05/cer-board-recommends-that-securityholders-vote-for-resolutions.html
Centro Retail Trust and Centro Retail
Ltd., together CER, released the CER Explanatory Memorandum on
the proposed aggregation and the disclosure document in relation
to the proposed new A-REIT.  “CER board concluded aggregation is in best interests of
CER securityholders. Accordingly, CER board (other than those
directors who are also directors of CNP, who make no
recommendation) unanimously recommend CER securityholders vote
in favour of resolutions to effect aggregation in absence of
superior proposal,” according to a statement today.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Colin Keatinge at 
 ckeatinge@bloomberg.net  